    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a happy fiddle leaf fig, you need a soil mix that is very fast-draining and airy to prevent root rot, which is a major concern for these plants. A blend of 50% orchid bark and 50% perlite or pumice is often the gold standard, as it mimics the loose, open structure of a fiddle leaf fig's natural habitat. You can also add a handful of perlite to your standard potting soil to increase aeration and ensure water doesn't pool around the roots. Avoid heavy, water-retentive garden soils or standard potting mixes unless you significantly amend them with coarse ingredients like orchid bark. Using the right mix will help the roots establish immediately and keep the plant healthy after repotting.",
